The holiday, also known as May Day, has its roots in the historical struggles of workers and their trade unions to achieve fair employment standards. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Wednesday is Workers' Day -  a day dedicated to the struggle of workers. WATCH: eThekwini municipal workers strike In South Africa, Workers' Day has officially been observed since 1994. WATCH: Japan workers not pleased with 10-day holiday The holiday, also known as May Day, has its roots in the historical struggles of workers and their trade unions to achieve fair employment standards.
Workers' Day or May Day, only became an official public holiday after the democratic elections of 1994. 
However, calls for better working conditions date back as far as the 1800s  most notably after the uprisings in Europe and the United States. eNCA's Janke Tolmay unpacks the day's history.